This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image processing and analysis. The use of deep neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed method involves detecting cracks on pavement surfaces, which could fall under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper also deals with the issue of road safety, which could make it relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
